        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_PreProcessFinalCheckOfGasBillsAdjustments",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to process adjustments related to gas billing for accounts and meters. It updates records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Gas.UploadMeterBillingAdjustmentGas",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Gas.UploadAccountBillingAdjustmentGas",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " tables by joining them with corresponding records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.AccountExchangeMeterTrack",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.Account",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.Meter",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " tables. The procedure also calculates the number of unknown accounts and meters, which are those without corresponding sequence IDs, and returns these counts as output parameters. The procedure concludes by setting a status code to indicate successful execution."
        }
      ]
